File: A man prays during the month of Ramadan. JOHANNESBURG - The Council of Muslim Theologians has slammed police for arresting worshippers. It’s calling for an investigation into the conduct of SAPS members. SA Lockdown: Bridal couple and guests arrested on wedding day This follows an incident that has gone viral on social media where police stormed a prayer gathering in Pretoria and arrested 17 men. They face charges of contravening the Disaster Management Act regulations as they relate to the Covid-19 lockdown. READ: South Africa's COVID-19 death toll climbs to 86 In the video, a police officer can be heard chastising the group. The council says it accepts that officers have to enforce the law but says it's appalled by their heavy-handedness. Religious gatherings have been banned to curb the spread of the coronavirus.